  "notes": "Primary data from the official RFEG club page (all per-hole par, hcp, meters, Vc/Vs read directly from the page's scorecard tables). Stroke index is identical across all rated tees and genders on the RFEG card. Hole19 independently confirms the exact same par sequence and SI allocation (its yellow-tee distances differ by a few meters, likely an older survey). Verified: pars sum to 72, SIs are a permutation of 1-18, each tee's 18 distances sum exactly to the RFEG totals (6201/5891/5517/4960 m). Distances are gender-independent per tee color; men's and women's entries share the same meters with different Vc/Vs. Discrepancies: the club's legacy website (elplantio.com) shows an older scorecard with different SI (e.g. hole 2 hcp 14 vs 16) and slightly different distances; GolfPass's often-quoted 73.4/133 rating actually matches RFEG's current Rojas women's rating, not the men's championship card. Separate on-site courses not included in this scorecard: 'Pares 3' (9 greens played as 18, par 54, 1848 m yellow men Vc 52/Vs 73; 1780 m red women Vc 53.7/Vs 79) and a rated P&P Verdes recorrido (1558 m, Vc 49.8/Vs 58 men, 51.5/67 women)."
